claim.claim-text:
1. A motion sensing system comprising: 
at least one piezoelectric laminate; 
at least one electrode disposed on said piezoelectric laminate; 
a frequency selector, coupled to said electrode, for passing motion waves of predetermined frequencies; 
an electrical circuit, coupled to said frequency selector, for processing electrical signals from said frequency selector; and 
an activating device, coupled to said electrical circuit, for activation in response to the electrical signals.

22. An electronic storage device comprising: 
a magnetic disk for storing information; 
a disk drive, coupled to said magnetic disk, for driving said magnetic disk; 
a read/write head; 
a servo-mechanism, coupled to said disk drive and to said read/write head, for controlling the relative positions and motions of said magnetic disk and said read/write head; and 
a sensing device, disposed on said electronic storage device and coupled to said servo-mechanism, for sensing motions of said magnetic disk storage device, and transmitting signals to said servo-mechanism.

28. A method of sensing a motion, comprising the steps of: 
(a) sensing the motion as a wave motion utilizing a piezoelectric laminate having a plurality of electrodes disposed thereon; 
(b) collecting electrical signals generated by said wave motion on said piezoelectric laminate; 
(c) transmitting the wave motion-generated electrical signals to a bandpass filter; 
(d) filtering said wave motion-generated electrical signals utilizing said bandpass filter; 
(e) generating an activation signal responsive to said filtered wave motion-generated electrical signals; and 
(f) transmitting said activation signal to an activating device.

32. A method for sensing wave motion utilizing piezoelectric laminates having a distributed surface electrode modal sensor array disposed thereon, comprising the steps of: 
generating said distributed surface electrode modal sensor array utilizing a normal mode expansion; 
determining the boundary conditions responsive to the shape of the piezoelectric laminates; 
spatially filtering the wave motion to generate a characteristic polynomial wave transmission spatial bandpass filter; and 
adjusting the frequency response of the spatial bandpass filter to increase the bandwidth; thereby providing a method for detection of different types of wave motions.

33. A method for sensing wave motion utilizing piezoelectric laminates having a distributed surface electrode modal sensor array disposed thereon, comprising the steps of: 
collecting the charge generated by deformations in the piezoelectric laminates utilizing the distributed surface electrode modal sensor array to generate a characteristic wave; 
spatial modal filtering said characteristic wave to generate characteristic electrical signals; 
parallel processing said characteristic electrical signals to determine the motion sensed.
